## Keep App Alive

This project demonstrates a simple approach to keeping a deployed Streamlit application active by sending periodic requests to the app. Many free hosting platforms may put applications to sleep after a period of inactivity, which can increase the loading time for users. By automating regular health-check requests, the app remains responsive and is less likely to become inactive.

The project is lightweight, easy to configure, and suitable for beginners who want to learn about Python automation, HTTP requests, and maintaining the availability of deployed web applications.
